Groups, Roles, and Rights
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s23\ql \li0\ri0\sb60\sa60\nowidctlpar\intbl\tx0\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\pararsid10951181\yts20 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs20\lang1036\langfe1033\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\cgrid\langnp1036\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\alang1081 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\insrsid6163624\charrsid4591722 \hich\af37\dbch\af31505\loch\f37 
Users are able to perform tasks and gain access to specific features in XXX based on the rights held by their user account. To gain rights, user accounts must belong to the groups you set up in User Setup.
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af31505\loch\f37 By grouping user accounts, you can organize users \hich\af37\dbch\af31505\loch\f37 
and control the scope of their access within XXX. Using groups, roles, and rights, you can enhance the security of XXX, steer users to targeted content, and ensure that anonymous users are, automatically given appropriate rights.
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af31505\loch\f37 Groups are based on the ro\hich\af37\dbch\af31505\loch\f37 les they are assigned, while roles are based on the rights they are assigned. Rights, roles, and groups are defined as follows\~:
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \s22 \intbl\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20\alang1081 \ltrch\fcs0 \f3\fs20\insrsid6163624\charrsid4591722 \loch\af3\dbch\af31505\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard\plain \ltrpar\s22\ql \fi-357\li357\ri0\sb60\sa60\nowidctlpar\intbl
\jclisttab\tx360\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls2\adjustright\rin0\lin357\pararsid10951181\yts20 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 
\af37\alang1081 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\insrsid6163624\charrsid4591722 \hich\af37\dbch\af31505\loch\f37 A right is a permission to perform a specific task.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \s22 \intbl\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20\alang1081 \ltrch\fcs0 \f3\fs20\insrsid6163624\charrsid4591722 \loch\af3\dbch\af31505\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}\hich\af37\dbch\af31505\loch\f37 
A role is a set of rights typically consisting of a set of related righ\hich\af37\dbch\af31505\loch\f37 ts that should be assigned together. However, you can create a role from any of the rights available in XXX.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \s22 \intbl\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\afs20\alang1081 \ltrch\fcs0 \f3\fs20\insrsid6163624\charrsid4591722 \loch\af3\dbch\af31505\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}\hich\af37\dbch\af31505\loch\f37 
A group is a set of roles that defines the scope of a user account. Users can belong to more than one group, and their overall scope is determine\hich\af37\dbch\af31505\loch\f37 d, by all of the rights they have.
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s16\ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\intbl\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\pararsid10951181\yts20 \rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af31505\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
