Understanding the Controller, Chassis, and I/O Modules for a XXX System
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s23\ql \li0\ri0\sb60\sa60\nowidctlpar\intbl\tx0\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\pararsid13197593\yts20 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs20\lang1036\langfe1033\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\cgrid\langnp1036\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\alang1081 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\insrsid6163624\charrsid13197593 \hich\af37\dbch\af31505\loch\f37 
Control hardware includes a Chassis (Rack), Power Supply, 1757-PLX52 Control Processor, XXX Interface, Redundancy Module, and I/O Modules. An optional Battery Extension Module (not sho\hich\af37\dbch\af31505\loch\f37 
wn) is also available. The Chassis is available in 5 sizes - 4, 7, 10, 13, and 17 slots.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \s23 \intbl\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20\alang1081 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid6163624\charrsid13197593 \hich\af37\dbch\af31505\loch\f37 1.\tab}}\pard \ltrpar\s23\ql \fi-360\li720\ri0\sb60\sa60\nowidctlpar\intbl
\tx0\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls3\adjustright\rin0\lin720\pararsid13197593\yts20 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af37\alang1081 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\insrsid6163624\charrsid13197593 \hich\af37\dbch\af31505\loch\f37 
The Power Supply is separate from the Rack and does not consume any slots. It is mounted on the left end of the Rack. Both 120/240 VAC and 24 VDC supplies are avail\hich\af37\dbch\af31505\loch\f37 able.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \s23 \intbl\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20\alang1081 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\fs20\insrsid6163624\charrsid13197593 \hich\af37\dbch\af31505\loch\f37 2.\tab}\hich\af37\dbch\af31505\loch\f37 
The 1757-PLX52 Process Control Module is a double wide, two-board assembly featuring a 100 MHz PowerPC processor and eight (8) Mbytes of RAM with error detection and correction. It supports both non-redundant and redundant controller configuration
\hich\af37\dbch\af31505\loch\f37 
s. Four (4) Mbytes of parity-protected Flash ROM is used for permanent program storage and allows easy upgrades. A built-in lithium battery backs up the controller database, and an optional two-slot wide Battery Extension Module provides a rechargeable op
\hich\af37\dbch\af31505\loch\f37 t\hich\af37\dbch\af31505\loch\f37 ion instead of replacing the lithium battery.
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s16\ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\intbl\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\pararsid13197593\yts20 \rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af31505\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
